issues.description: The SNMP configuration has Virtual Connect Manager trap categories selected that are not supported by OneView.
issues.recommendation: Virtual Connect Manager trap categories contains Domain Status, FC Status, Server Status, Network Status, Profile Status, Fabric Status, and Enet Status which are not supported by OneView. These categories will be removed.

issues.description: SMIS is disabled.
issues.recommendation: SMIS will be enabled automatically.

issues.description: The boot mode in profile Profile08 is configured as Auto and some PXE, FC, and FCoE connections are not configured to boot BIOS.
issues.recommendation: Configure all PXE, FC, and FCoE connections to boot from BIOS, or change the boot mode to something other than Auto.

issues.description: Profile Profile08 has one or more connections configured with Use-BIOS boot settings. OneView does not support profile connections configured with a mixture of Use-BIOS and other boot settings.
issues.recommendation: The Virtual Connect Use-BIOS boot setting will be automatically changed to not bootable in OneView.

issues.description: Profile Profile08 Ethernet connection 6 does not have an associated network. This connection will not be migrated because OneView does not allow server profile connections without an assigned network.
issues.recommendation: To migrate the server profile connection, assign a network to this connection. If virtual MAC addresses are configured, assigning a network to this connection will preserve these addresses.

issues.description: Profile Profile08 FCoE connection 2 does not have an associated fabric. This connection will not be migrated because OneView does not allow server profile connections without an assigned network.
issues.recommendation: To migrate the server profile connection, assign a fabric to this connection. If virtual WWN addresses are configured, assigning a fabric to this connection will preserve these addresses.

issues.description: The profile Profile08 Ethernet connection number 7 is not associated with a downlink port in the current IO module configuration. OneView does not support connections which are not associated with a downlink port.
issues.recommendation: If no action is taken, the connection will be migrated to OneView with the port configuration set to none.
